===Etymology===
[[File:Tetramorph meteora.jpg|thumb|A cherub, as described by Ezekiel]]

From {{inh|en|enm|cherubin}}, {{m|enm|cherub}}, {{m|enm|cherube}}, {{m|enm|cherubine}}, {{m|enm|cherubym}}, {{m|enm|cherubyn}}, {{m|enm|cherybin}}, {{m|enm|gerubin}}, {{m|enm|jerubin}},<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=cherubin|pos=n|id=MED7474|accessdate=19 August 2019}}</ref> from {{inh|en|ang|cerubin}}, {{m|ang|cerubim}}, {{m|ang|cherubin}}, from {{der|en|la|cherūbīn}}, {{m|la|cherūbīm}}, {{glossary|plural}} of {{der|en|la|cherub|t=cherub}}, from {{der|en|grc|χερούβ}}, ultimately from {{der|en|he|כרוב|כְּרוּב|tr=kerúv}}; further {{unknown|en|etymology uncertain}}.<ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=n|id=31359|date=1889|nodot=yes}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=n}}</ref>

The plural form {{m|en|cherubim}} is from {{der|en|he|כְּרוּבִים|tr=k'ruvím}}.

